//
// T048: `%IDENT%` macro splices are byte-preserved (research §7).
//
// The M1 lexer (per `lib/Lex/Lexer.cpp` FR-037 amendment) folds
// `%IDENT%` into the SURROUNDING identifier when the splice
// appears INSIDE an identifier body (e.g., `mod_%FOO%`). Bare
// `%FOO%` not adjacent to an identifier prefix is NOT recognised
// — that's a parse error per Q1 strict refusal (Session
// 2026-05-05). So this fixture exercises the inline-residue form
// which is what the M1 lexer actually supports.

// RUN: echo 'module mod_%%FOO%% {}' | nsl-fmt --stdin | FileCheck %s
// CHECK: module mod_%FOO% {}
